OL,3,CAdvert banned over complimentary food
OL,4,Cand drink claims on train services
OL,6,FAn ad for CrossCountry Trains has been
OL,7,Fbanned for over-promising on the
OL,8,Favailability of complimentary food and
OL,9,Fdrink for first-class passengers.
OL,11,FDespite the firm's website claiming
OL,12,Fpassengers would receive complimentary
OL,13,Ffood and drink "on most of our first-
OL,14,Fclass services", catering was
OL,15,Favailable on less than 80% of
OL,16,Fjourneys, the Advertising Standards
OL,17,FAuthority (ASA) found.
