OL,3,CAdvert banned over complimentary food
OL,4,Cand drink claims on train services
OL,6,FThe website said: "An at-seat service
OL,7,Fof complimentary non-alcoholic drinks
OL,8,Fand snacks is available throughout the
OL,9,Fday for all first-class customers ...
OL,10,FIn addition to drinks and snacks,
OL,11,Fcustomers on longer journeys can
OL,12,Fchoose from a range of complimentary
OL,13,Fsandwiches."
OL,15,FTwo passengers who said they
OL,16,Ffrequently travelled on the first-
OL,17,Fclass service but did not receive
OL,18,Fcomplimentary food and drink
OL,19,Fcomplained that the ad was misleading.
