OL,3,CAdvert banned over complimentary food
OL,4,Cand drink claims on train services
OL,6,FThe ASA said the ad "positioned
OL,7,Fcomplimentary food and drink as a key
OL,8,Fpart of CrossCountry Trains' first-
OL,9,Fclass offering".
OL,11,FIt said the scheduled rate of between
OL,12,F70% and 78% of services offering
OL,13,Fcatering was insufficient to
OL,14,Fsubstantiate the overall impression of
OL,15,Fthe ad that complimentary food and
OL,16,Fdrink would be available on all but a
OL,17,Ffew first-class services.
