OL,3,CAdvert banned over complimentary food
OL,4,Cand drink claims on train services
OL,6,FThe ASA said: "We acknowledged that
OL,7,FCrossCountry Trains had made
OL,8,Famendments to their website, but for
OL,9,Fthe reasons stated above, we concluded
OL,10,Fthat the claim 'complimentary food and
OL,11,Fdrink' was misleading, and therefore
OL,12,Fbreached the Code."
OL,14,FIt ruled that the ad must not appear
OL,15,Fagain, adding: "We told CrossCountry
OL,16,FTrains not to use the claim
OL,17,F'complimentary food and drink' unless
OL,18,Fthey held adequate evidence to
OL,19,Fsubstantiate the claim."
